{
  "stem": "1799.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "What was unusual about this task was that more often than not, one of the corpses in the-- in the buggy that'd be carried, in the cart that'd be carried in, was one of the guys that helped to dig the grave the day before.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And it occurred to me that, you know, if I didn't survive this-- this situation-- it was early spring but it was winter, and things were cold-- things were not pleasant-- that I might very well end up being in one of those graves myself.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But it did not happen.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I did survive.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And towards the end of April, we-- we did not continue this process.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Because one morning, as an example, one morning the-- there were no guards at all around the camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the Germans had left.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I remember hearing shooting, and cannons, and bombs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And so we knew that something was happening.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And there were maybe 50 people alive in the camp, which originally was 300 people.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And we-- that's when we took potatoes-- we knew where they were stored-- and would make fires by using even old barracks, old bedposts, or old posts and wood, lumber, that we could find, and roast the potatoes in the ashes of and embers of those fires.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "That was our only food.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] That lasted about four or five days.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "[SIGHS] Then one day, May 1, early in the morning, the guards having left, there was an American jeep that came into the center of the courtyard of the camp.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And-- officer, with a driver, and the officer put his foot on the pavement.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I walked towards him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he said, who are you?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I identified myself.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he said, where are the German guards?",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
